### Translate Resources in Client Component (React)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/custom-components/overview.mdx

Illustrates how to translate text resources in a React Client Component using the `useTranslation` hook from `@payloadcms/ui`. This hook provides `t` for translation and access to the `i18n` object.

```tsx
'use client'
import React from 'react'
import { useTranslation } from '@payloadcms/ui'

export function MyClientComponent() {
  const { t, i18n } = useTranslation()

  return (
    <ul>
      <li>{t('namespace1:key', { variable: 'value' })}</li>
      <li>{t('namespace2:key', { variable: 'value' })}</li>
      <li>{i18n.language}</li>
    </ul>
  )
}
```

